	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If the "easy" in quotes was about my comment, I said "easier" not easy. If not, nevermind.
<br />
<br />Most FDS games can be emulated fairly easily thanks to Brad Taylor's FDS document that tells you the BIOS function call addresses for important things like LoadFiles(). This is how I added FDS support. Rather than implement all the garbage to work with FDS I just hook any subroutine calls for disk access like LoadFiles() and execute the same thing in C++ code. It beats emulating the actual drive. :p And it loads instantly which is nice.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


